description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit a Physician Associate to work at Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The PA will work within the Emergency Department. Post holders will be required to work a variety of shifts covering a 7 day rota from 8am until midnight. Post holders will form part of the multidisciplinary team. They will work cross site between Epsom and St Helier Hospitals. We already have 13 PAs working in the department with a further seven working across the hospitals. The trust has employed PAs since 2011 and has long established links with the local university. You will have a dedicated consultant supervisor and lead PA who will oversee your development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have initial funding guaranteed until April 2021 with potential to extend beyond this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be accountable for ensuring that patient care is of a high standard at all times and that standards of care and treatment meet the department’s requirements. Please see the attached job descriptions for further details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amy Tullin, Lead Physician Associate Emergency Medicine - amy.tullin@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
